<subSubSection id="C365E9955801B572FF5DEB91FE33FD8F" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC0BA1E5801B572FF5DEB91FE33FD8F" blockId="4.[151,1436,474,570]" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis id="B90B660C5801B572FF5DEB91FEDCFE46" bold="true" box="[151,273,474,499]" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Epandrial lobe bifurcated with short thick anterior process and long finger-like posterior process; surstylus strongly curved forward. Legs black except extreme tips of all femora brownish. Fore femur with distinct av shorter than femur thickness.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
