<subSubSection id="C365E9955800B573FF0FEADCFE76FCB3" pageId="5" pageNumber="64" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC0BA1E5800B573FF0FEADCFB37FE89" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,951]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis id="B90B660C5800B573FF0FEADCFE51FF05" bold="true" box="[197,412,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64">Description. Male</emphasis>
. Body length 
<quantity id="4C8717FB5800B573FD8AEADCFD54FF1A" box="[576,665,151,175]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity id="4C8717FB5800B573FCFDEADCFC5FFF1A" box="[823,914,151,175]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
. Head black with pale gray pollen. Eyes very narrowly separated on face, brownish. Setae and setulae on head black except posteroventral surface with pale setulae; ocellar tubercle distinct with pair of long oc. Antenna black; first flagellomere long conical, 
<number id="3DB7A8395800B573FB14EA95FACDFF43" box="[1246,1280,222,246]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64" value="1.8">1.8</number>
X longer than wide; arista very long, 
<number id="3DB7A8395800B573FE52EB4AFE77FEAC" box="[408,442,257,281]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64" value="2.3">2.3</number>
X length of flagellomere; arista very short micropubescent. Proboscis long, 
<number id="3DB7A8395800B573FAC7EB4AFAFDFEAC" box="[1293,1328,257,281]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64" value="0.9">0.9</number>
X as long as head height, blackish with blackish setulae. Palpus black with 
<number id="3DB7A8395800B573FCBAEB6FFCB3FE89" box="[880,894,292,316]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64" value="4.0">4</number>
black setulae (
<number id="3DB7A8395800B573FBE2EB6FFBF9FE89" box="[1064,1076,292,316]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
apical seta long).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC0BA1E5800B573FF0FEB0CFC97FDBA" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,951]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64">
Thorax black with pale grey pollen. Setae and setulae on thorax black; pronotum with 
<number id="3DB7A8395800B573FB69EB0CFB7CFEEA" box="[1187,1201,327,351]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
seta laterally; 
<number id="3DB7A8395800B573FA90EB0CFAA5FEEA" box="[1370,1384,327,351]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
h, 
<number id="3DB7A8395800B573FA44EB0CFA51FEEA" box="[1422,1436,327,351]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
npl, 
<number id="3DB7A8395800B573FF03EB20FF1AFE36" box="[201,215,363,387]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64" value="3.0">3</number>
short acr, 
<number id="3DB7A8395800B573FE86EB20FE97FE36" box="[332,346,363,387]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64" value="5.0">5</number>
dc, 
<number id="3DB7A8395800B573FE43EB20FE5AFE36" box="[393,407,363,387]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
psa; scutellum with 
<number id="3DB7A8395800B573FDB5EB20FD40FE36" box="[639,653,363,387]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
setae. Legs black except extreme tips of all femora brownish. Setulae and setae on legs black except those on coxae pale; fore femur basally with row of 
<number id="3DB7A8395800B573FBF0EBC5FBA9FE13" box="[1082,1124,398,422]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
pale av setae (longest setae shorter than femur thickness), mid and hind femora with short pale av setulae. Fore femur 
<number id="3DB7A8395800B573FB67EBFAFB03FE7C" box="[1197,1230,433,457]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64" value="1.1">1.1</number>
X as thick as mid femur, mid and hind femora subequal in thickness. Wing hyaline, slightly tinged grayish; veins dark brown. Squama dark yellow, bordered with pale setulae. Halter brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC0BA1E5800B573FF0FE850FD28FD75" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,951]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64">
Abdomen blackish with pale gray pollen except hypopygium black. Setulae and setae on abdomen blackish. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="1344A69B5800B573FE82E875FE7BFDE3" box="[328,438,574,598]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 6" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1899,1922]" captionTargetBox="[236,1334,626,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[222,1365,623,1878]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 6. Heleodromia (Heleodromia) immaculata Haliday (male). 5. Tergite 8, dorsal view. 6. Genitalia, lateral view. Abbreviations: apel = anterior process of epandrial lobe; ppel = posterior process of epandrial lobe; sur = surstylus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279711/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="64">
Figs. 
<number id="3DB7A8395800B573FE4DE875FE7BFDE3" box="[391,438,574,598]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
</figureCitation>
): tergite 
<number id="3DB7A8395800B573FDD2E875FDEBFDE3" box="[536,550,574,598]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64" value="8.0">8</number>
and sternite 
<number id="3DB7A8395800B573FD7DE875FD08FDE3" box="[695,709,574,598]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64" value="8.0">8</number>
rather small; tergite 
<number id="3DB7A8395800B573FC65E875FC70FDE3" box="[943,957,574,598]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64" value="8.0">8</number>
wide posteriorly, without any processes at posterior margin. Epandrium and hypandrium much elongated and rather large; epandrium distinctly shorter than hypandrium in lateral view. Epandrial lobe bifurcated with short thick anterior process and long finger-like posterior process; surstylus strongly curved forward.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC0BA1E5800B573FF0FE880FE76FCB3" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,951]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis id="B90B660C5800B573FF0FE880FED1FD56" bold="true" box="[197,284,715,739]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64">Female</emphasis>
. Body length 3.0 mm, wing length 
<quantity id="4C8717FB5800B573FD72E880FCDEFD56" box="[696,787,715,739]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
. Similar to male, but palpus with 
<number id="3DB7A8395800B573FB50E880FB65FD56" box="[1178,1192,715,739]" pageId="5" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
long apical setae, all femora with short pale av.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
